OL,3,CPost Office involved in 'possible
OL,4,Ccriminal conspiracy', investigator says
OL,6,FHe accused the Post Office of refusing
OL,7,Fto commission an independent review
OL,8,Finto the scandal, adding he faced
OL,9,F"various threats" of legal action from
OL,10,Fthe company, which appeared to include
OL,11,F"defamation, breach of confidence or
OL,12,Fbreach of contract".
OL,14,FMr Henderson said despite Ms Vennells
OL,15,Ftelling him the Post Office was the
OL,16,F"nation's most trusted brand", he
OL,17,Fbelieved the company felt it was
OL,18,F"above the law".
OL,20,FRon Warmington gives evidence at the
OL,21,Finquiry
